[NOTE RUN_WITH_MAIN_CAMPAIGN]
scope = vicreg.solo execution
text = main_campaign is a single-binding worker surface, not a full sequential campaign dispatcher. Use it when you want one bind explicitly: /cuwacunu/.build/hero/main_campaign --global-config /cuwacunu/src/config/.config --campaign-dsl /cuwacunu/src/config/instructions/objectives/vicreg.solo/iitepi.campaign.dsl --binding bind_train_vicreg_smoke --reset-runtime-state

[NOTE RUN_WITH_RUNTIME_HERO_DEFAULT]
scope = vicreg.solo execution
text = Runtime Hero is the surface that executes the campaign RUN list in order. To run the vicreg.solo default plan (currently primary-train then eval), pass the objective campaign explicitly: /cuwacunu/.build/hero/hero_runtime_mcp --global-config /cuwacunu/src/config/.config --tool hero.runtime.start_campaign --args-json '{"campaign_dsl_path":"/cuwacunu/src/config/instructions/objectives/vicreg.solo/iitepi.campaign.dsl","reset_runtime_state":true}'

[NOTE RUN_WITH_RUNTIME_HERO_BIND]
scope = vicreg.solo execution
text = To run only one vicreg.solo bind and ignore the campaign RUN list for that launch: /cuwacunu/.build/hero/hero_runtime_mcp --global-config /cuwacunu/src/config/.config --tool hero.runtime.start_campaign --args-json '{"campaign_dsl_path":"/cuwacunu/src/config/instructions/objectives/vicreg.solo/iitepi.campaign.dsl","binding_id":"bind_train_vicreg_ablation_short","reset_runtime_state":true}'

[NOTE ARCH_SWEEP_START]
scope = vicreg.solo execution
text = Recommended first architecture sweep under big_span_v1: bind_train_vicreg_ablation_short (baseline), bind_train_vicreg_ablation_small, bind_train_vicreg_ablation_wide, and bind_train_vicreg_ablation_deep. Then run the matching holdout evaluators bind_eval_vicreg_payload, bind_eval_vicreg_payload_small, bind_eval_vicreg_payload_wide, and bind_eval_vicreg_payload_deep before promoting any candidate to a primary train bind

[NOTE MONITOR_RUNTIME]
scope = vicreg.solo execution
text = Monitor state with hero.runtime.list_campaigns, hero.runtime.get_campaign, hero.runtime.list_jobs, hero.runtime.tail_log, and hero.runtime.tail_trace. Example: /cuwacunu/.build/hero/hero_runtime_mcp --global-config /cuwacunu/src/config/.config --tool hero.runtime.list_campaigns --args-json '{}'

[NOTE EVALUATE_REPORTS]
scope = vicreg.solo evaluation
text = Evaluation should compare the emitted VICReg runtime .lls evidence, especially status, embedding-sequence analytics, symbolic embedding analytics, and transfer-matrix reports. Transfer-matrix evaluation is owned by the VICReg objective itself and defaults to the active observation feature dimensions, while still allowing an optional probe-local mdn_target_dims override when we want a narrower evaluation question. In vicreg.solo, the contract-scoped __future_target_dims variable coordinates EXPECTED_VALUE.target_dims and transfer-matrix-eval mdn_target_dims without creating a runtime dependency between the modules. Runtime Hero gives campaign/job lineage; Hashimyei/Lattice give the comparable report surface. A useful starting query is hero.lattice.get_view with view_kind=family_evaluation_report, canonical_path=tsi.wikimyei.representation.vicreg, and the relevant contract_hash.

[NOTE REPORT_READING_ORDER]
scope = vicreg.solo evaluation
text = Read reports in this order: 1) Runtime Hero tail_trace/tail_log for structural health and progress; 2) status.latest.lls for trained steps/epochs and source_runtime_cursor; 3) embedding_sequence_analytics.v2.latest.lls and embedding_sequence_analytics.symbolic.v2.latest.lls for representation quality clues; 4) transfer_matrix_evaluation.summary.latest.lls and transfer_matrix_evaluation.matrix.latest.lls for probe-style transfer evidence; 5) family_evaluation_report views for holdout comparison across promoted candidates

[NOTE REFINEMENT_LOOP]
scope = vicreg.solo research loop
text = Recommended loop: 1) keep big_span_v1 observation channels fixed; 2) run the architecture sweep first through bind_train_vicreg_smoke[_small|_wide|_deep] and bind_train_vicreg_ablation_short/_small/_wide/_deep; 3) run the matching holdout evaluators bind_eval_vicreg_payload[_small|_wide|_deep]; 4) inspect tail_trace plus latest .lls evidence for collapse, instability, or weak structure; 5) promote only the strongest architecture candidate to its matching bind_train_vicreg_primary* path; 6) run the matching bind_eval_vicreg_payload* on the holdout split after the full train; 7) only after architecture is stable, start a narrow jkimyei profile sweep through __jk_profile_id; 8) keep the revision only if holdout reports improve without breaking runtime stability

[NOTE SUPER_LOOP_V1]
scope = vicreg.solo research loop
text = Super Hero is now the bounded loop owner under `<runtime_root>/.super_hero/<loop_id>/`, launched with `hero.super.start_loop(...)`. For vicreg.solo, the loop starts from `vicreg.solo.super.dsl`, which points to `iitepi.campaign.dsl` plus separate `vicreg.solo.objective.md` and shared `default.super.guidance.md`; Super Hero copies those into the loop ledger, points its mutable `objective_root` at the truth-source objective bundle under `src/config/instructions/objectives/vicreg.solo/`, then assembles `super.briefing.md` and the loop-local `config.hero.policy.dsl`. Codex returns `control_kind = continue | stop | need_human`, any `continue` must carry a bounded validated next action, and during review Codex may use loop-scoped `hero.config.objective_dsl.read/replace` plus bounded Runtime/Lattice read tools directly against that objective truth source and persisted evidence, but not against source `campaign.dsl` or source `vicreg.solo.super.dsl`. Runtime Hero still snapshots each launch from the truth source. The intended first use remains architecture refinement across the existing baseline/small/wide/deep binds only.

[RULE OBJECTIVE_PROMOTION_GUARD]
id = OBJECTIVE_PROMOTION_GUARD
applies_to = vicreg.solo refinement loop
severity = info
when = candidate is promoted to primary without smoke and short-ablation evidence
message = prefer smoke -> short ablation -> primary train -> holdout eval; skip stages only when the change is operationally trivial
